Class DatasetIdentifier

  • java.lang.Object
    • eu.smartdatalake.simsearch.DatasetIdentifier

  • public class DatasetIdentifier
extends Object
    Provides identification for the data regarding a specific attribute available from a data source.

      • DatasetIdentifier

        public DatasetIdentifier(DataSource source,
                         String dataset,
                         String colValueName)
        Parameters:
        source - The data source (directory, JDBC connection, or REST API) that provides access to the attribute data.
        dataset - The name of the dataset (file, table) that contains the attribute data.
        colValueName - The column name containing the attribute data to be used.

        public void setOperation(int operation)
        Assign the type of the search operation to the identifier.
        Parameters:
        operation - An integer representing the type of the search operation (0: CATEGORICAL_TOPK; 1:SPATIAL_KNN ; 2:NUMERICAL_TOPK).

      • setDataSource

        public void setDataSource(DataSource source)
        Assign a data source to the identifier.
        Parameters:
        source - The data source providing the attribute values, either in-memory (CSV) or in-situ (JDBC).

      • setQueryable

        public void setQueryable(boolean queryable)
        Specify that this attribute data will be involved or not in similarity search requests.
        Parameters:
        queryable - Boolean value: True, if this attribute may be specified in similarity search queries; otherwise, False.

      • setPrefixURL

        public void setPrefixURL(String prefixURL)
        Prefix to be used in composing URLs and issuing them as entity identifiers in similarity search results.
        Parameters:
        prefixURL - The prefix to be appended to the entity identifiers (coming from values in attrKey).
